{"image_id": "PMC5662230_5", "image_size": [773, 1000], "ocr": [{"text": "Dapsone in ITP", "bbox": [659.8, 50.5, 727.3, 60.6]}, {"text": "Table 2. Outcome on dapsone therapy.", "bbox": [45.5, 97.3, 228.6, 107.4]}, {"text": "All patients Non-responders Responders Complete Partial response p-value *", "bbox": [277.4, 114.3, 723.5, 126.4]}, {"text": "response", "bbox": [524.5, 128.0, 569.3, 138.1]}, {"text": "(n = 42) (n = 19) (n = 23) (n = 16) (n = 7)", "bbox": [287.0, 143.8, 648.3, 153.9]}, {"text": "Course of ITP at dapsone initiation, months 8.8 (2–53.6) 7.5 (2.3–57.9) 9.6 (1.6–49.9) 2.2 (1.2–18.7) 49.9 (38.5–90.9) 0.009", "bbox": [45.5, 159.6, 714.2, 169.7]}, {"text": "Course of ITP at dapsone initiation 0.03", "bbox": [45.5, 175.4, 708.6, 185.5]}, {"text": "Newly diagnosed, n (%) 14 5 9 9 0", "bbox": [55.5, 191.1, 636.6, 201.2]}, {"text": "Persistent, n (%) 9 6 3 2 1", "bbox": [55.5, 206.9, 636.6, 217.0]}, {"text": "Chronic, n (%) 19 8 11 5 6", "bbox": [55.5, 222.7, 636.6, 232.8]}, {"text": "Time to response, days 29 (24–41) / 29 (24–41) 28.5 (24–44) 32 (23–41) 0.84", "bbox": [45.5, 238.5, 708.6, 248.6]}, {"text": "Response duration, months 7.5 (3.5–19.4) / 7.5 (3.5–19.4) 10.4 (4.2–21.3) 3.9 (1.9–7.5) 0.05", "bbox": [45.5, 254.3, 708.6, 264.4]}, {"text": "Treatment duration, months 3.9 (1.6–9) 1.5 (0.6–2.4) 8.9 (5.1–19.8) 12.1 (5.2–23) 7.1 (2.5–8.9) 0.08", "bbox": [45.5, 270.1, 708.6, 280.2]}, {"text": "Relapse on dapsone therapy 5 (11.9%) / 5 (21.7%) 2 (12.5%) 3 (42.9%)", "bbox": [45.5, 285.8, 655.4, 295.9]}, {"text": "Time to relapse, months 8.1 (6.5–13.6) / 8.1 (6.5–13.6) 33.7 (20.9–46.4) 6.5 (4.6–10.1)", "bbox": [45.5, 301.6, 664.9, 311.7]}, {"text": "Number of patients with sustained response (> 6 5 (11.9%) / 5 (21.7%) 4 (25%) 1 (14.3%)", "bbox": [45.5, 316.1, 655.4, 327.5]}, {"text": "months) after dapsone cessation", "bbox": [45.5, 329.4, 189.7, 339.5]}, {"text": "Follow-up after dapsone cessation, months 21.1 (12.6–29.5) / 21.1 (12.6– 21.1 (7.5–29.5) 12.6", "bbox": [45.5, 345.2, 643.6, 355.3]}, {"text": "29.5)", "bbox": [453.6, 357.2, 476.5, 367.3]}, {"text": "Side effects 13 (31%) 7 (36.8%) 6 (26.1%) 3 (18.8%) 3 (42.9%)", "bbox": [45.5, 372.9, 655.4, 383.0]}, {"text": "Cutaneous toxicity 5 5 0 0 0", "bbox": [55.5, 388.8, 636.6, 398.9]}, {"text": "Methemoglobinemia 4 2 2 1 1", "bbox": [55.5, 404.5, 636.6, 414.6]}, {"text": "Withdrawal because of toxicity 9 7 2 0 2", "bbox": [55.5, 420.3, 636.6, 430.4]}, {"text": "Dosage adaptation because of toxicity 4 / 4 3 1", "bbox": [55.5, 436.1, 636.6, 446.2]}, {"text": "Haemoglobin level at dapsone initiation, g/dL 13.9 (12.9–14.9) 13.3 (12.9–14.8) 14 (13.3–15) 13.5 (12.8–14.2) 15 (13.9–15.8) 0.02", "bbox": [45.5, 451.8, 708.6, 461.9]}, {"text": "Decrease in haemoglobin level, g/dL 1.5 (0.6–2.1) 1 (0.4–2) 1.8 (0.9–2.5) 1.5 (0.6–2) 2.5 (2–2.9) 0.02", "bbox": [45.5, 467.6, 708.6, 477.7]}, {"text": "* Complete response versus partial response", "bbox": [45.5, 489.6, 244.9, 501.7]}, {"text": "https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0187296.t002", "bbox": [45.5, 513.7, 236.2, 524.3]}, {"text": "(5/23 responders: 21.7%; 5/42 patients of the whole cohort: 14%) after a median follow-up of", "bbox": [252.5, 549.5, 715.1, 562.1]}, {"text": "21.1 (12.6–29.5) months. A CR was maintained in 3, while 2 switched to a PR. Among these 5", "bbox": [252.5, 565.9, 720.1, 578.5]}, {"text": "patients with sustained response after dapsone discontinuation, 3 had a newly diagnosed ITP", "bbox": [252.5, 582.4, 717.8, 595.0]}, {"text": "and 2 a chronic ITP.", "bbox": [252.5, 598.8, 354.8, 611.4]}, {"text": "Ten patients were still responders under treatment after 5.9 (2.8–19.5) months. Dapsone", "bbox": [267.6, 615.2, 710.0, 627.8]}, {"text": "dosage was tapered in 7 of them, in order to withdraw dapsone (n = 4) or because of side", "bbox": [252.5, 631.5, 695.8, 644.2]}, {"text": "effects (n = 3). One patient was lost to follow-up after 4.2 months of response.", "bbox": [252.5, 648.0, 640.9, 660.6]}, {"text": "Regarding the 19 non-responders, a response was achieved with rituximab in 8/11, with", "bbox": [267.6, 664.4, 706.8, 677.0]}, {"text": "splenectomy in 3/5, with TPO-RA in 3/4, and with hydroxychloroquine in 1/2, while 3 patients", "bbox": [252.5, 680.8, 727.2, 693.4]}, {"text": "had a platelet count allowing a wait and watch attitude.", "bbox": [252.5, 697.3, 527.6, 709.9]}, {"text": "As expected, responders to dapsone required less second line treatments (30%, 7/23) com-", "bbox": [267.6, 713.7, 719.5, 726.3]}, {"text": "pared to non-responders (84%, 16/19) after a median follow-up of 67.6 (49.5–105.2) months.", "bbox": [252.5, 730.0, 717.0, 742.7]}, {"text": "Rituximab was used in 17% of responders compared to 58% of non-responders; splenectomy", "bbox": [252.5, 746.5, 717.7, 759.1]}, {"text": "was performed in 17% vs. 26% and TPO-RAs were used in 4% vs.21%, respectively, supporting", "bbox": [252.5, 760.8, 725.4, 776.9]}, {"text": "dapsone as an interesting medication to spare the use of expensive drugs or radical treatment", "bbox": [252.5, 779.3, 718.0, 791.9]}, {"text": "such as splenectomy.", "bbox": [252.5, 795.7, 357.5, 808.3]}, {"text": "Dapsone side-effects", "bbox": [252.5, 829.1, 392.5, 844.3]}, {"text": "Fifteen side effects were reported in 13 patients (31%), consistent with skin rash (n = 5),", "bbox": [252.5, 852.9, 691.0, 865.5]}, {"text": "including sulfone syndrome (n = 2), methemoglobinemia (n = 4), neuropathy (n = 3), dys-", "bbox": [252.5, 869.3, 706.5, 882.0]}, {"text": "pnoea (n = 1), fatigue (n = 1) and diarrhoea (n = 1). Symptomatic anaemia or severe", "bbox": [252.5, 885.7, 673.6, 898.4]}, {"text": "PLOS ONE | https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0187296 October 30, 2017 6 / 13", "bbox": [45.5, 946.7, 727.3, 956.8]}]}